notes.title: React
notes.content: React is a free and open-source front-end JavaScript library for building user interfaces based on UI components. It is maintained by Meta and a community of individual developers and companies.

notes.title: Components
notes.content: React components implement a render() method that takes input data and returns what to display. This example uses an XML-like syntax called JSX

notes.title: Pragmatic routing
notes.content: React components implement a render() method that takes input data and returns what to display. This example uses an XML-like syntax called JSX

notes.title: Angular
notes.content: Angular is a TypeScript-based free and open-source web application framework led by the Angular Team at Google and by a community of individuals and corporations. Angular is a complete rewrite from the same team that built AngularJS

notes.title: NodeJS
notes.content: What's theNode.js is an open-source, cross-platform, back-end JavaScript runtime environment that runs on a JavaScript Engine and executes JavaScript code outside a web browser, which was designed to build scalable network applications.
